**Emergency Steps:**  
- **Step 1:** If you smell gas, hear it escaping, or suspect a leak, immediately evacuate the area.  
- **Step 2:** Call 9-1-1 for emergency assistance and then contact PG&E at 1-800-743-5000.  
- **Step 3:** Do not use any potential sources of ignition, such as cell phones, flashlights, or matches, until you are at a safe distance.  
- **Step 4:** If necessary, turn off the gas at the main service shutoff valve. Do not turn it back on yourself; wait for a qualified professional.  
- **Step 5:** Once the area is safe, allow PG&E representatives to inspect and restore gas service, including relighting pilot lights if needed [pge.com](https://www.pge.com/en/outages-and-safety/safety/gas-safety.html).